# HTTPS reverse proxy for the developer manager.
#
# Caddy auto-provisions a Let's Encrypt cert for
# developers.progstrength.fitness on first request. DNS A record for
# that name lives in GoDaddy (where progstrength.fitness is managed)
# and points at the manager's Elastic IP (allocated by Terraform —
# see `terraform output -raw manager_public_ip`). EIP is stable across
# applies, so the GoDaddy edit is a one-time setup step.
#
# (block_internal) follows the application Caddyfile's pattern. Grafana
# serves a /metrics endpoint for self-scraping; Prometheus already
# scrapes it over the docker network, so the public path responds 404.

(block_internal) {
	@internal path /metrics
	respond @internal 404
}

developers.progstrength.fitness {
	import block_internal
	reverse_proxy grafana:3000
}
